<p>I want to pass DDL_c as a parameter to an Action in a controller, when the id between 1000 to 1500 it does pass it as a parameter , but when the DDL_c is 3048 then it doesnt pass the parameter not even the getJson works.</p>  <pre><code>//Here DDL_c it passes 1048 as a parameter but doesnt pass 3048     $("#DDL_c").click(function (coffee) {          $.getJSON("/Shipping/GetRadioButtonValues", { serviceid: $("#DDL_c").val().toString() }, function (e) {               $("#weight").val(e.Weight);             $("#qytid").val(e.Qty);             $("#amountid").val(e.Amount);             $("#fixedid").val(e.Fixed);  )} )}; </code></pre>  <p>Here is the Action Code in controller, Yes DDL_c is the service of Id from dropdownlist, which i want to pass to the below action.</p>  <pre><code> public ActionResult GetRadioButtonValues(int? serviceid)             {                 Shipping_ViewModel model = new Shipping_ViewModel();                 if (db.Shipping_Additional.Where(a =&gt; a.Serv_Type_ID == serviceid).FirstOrDefault() != null)                 {                     Shipping_Services a = db.Shipping_Services.Find(serviceid);                      return Json(new { Fixed = a.Apply_Fixed, Qty = a.Apply_QTY, Amount = a.Apply_Amount, Weight = a.Apply_Weight }, JsonRequestBehavior.AllowGet);                 }                 return View();             } </code></pre>  <p>Regards Hamad</p>